parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump gear can cause engine shutdown or failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when riding at high speeds.
symptoms: oil leakage under the engine/motor frame

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sticking valves can cause engine shutdown or failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when riding at high speeds.
The failure of the transmission gears can cause the rear wheel to lock, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Confusion regarding recall notices can lead to delayed or missed repairs, potentially causing accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: conflicting information from dealers and manufacturers

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the rear wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, which can result in accidents, injuries, or even death.
symptoms: Intermittent occurrences of transmission problems when shifting into second gear
the gear will slip into neutral
loud noise and hesitation inside the gear box
transmission "locks up" at highway speeds with no advance warnings

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the rear fender can lead to a loss of control of the motorcycle if the fender buckles and falls into contact with the rear tire, posing a significant safety risk to the rider.
symptoms: Cracks appear on the rear fender
which can progress to the fender buckling and falling into contact with the rear tire.
